                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d437">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/10840: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief of the United States Asiatic Fleet</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Yarnell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-26T16:20:00+08:00"
                            >October 26, 1937—4:20 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 26—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>0026. Following instructions given Commanding General Second Marine Brigade this
                    date: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In case of attack on the defense forces or noncombatants in the United
                            States sector by planes of any nationality fire may be opened on such
                            planes in self defense.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>This is an extension of the order already given to vessels of the United States
                    Asiatic Fleet authorizing them to take such action in case of attack.</p>
            </div>
